Neurosurgery Opportunities in Metro Southwest Ohio!!
(3 Openings) - Complex Spine, Neuro-ONC, General Neurosurgeon-Academic Interest in Trauma
Hospital and University in Metro Southwest Ohio are seeking 3 Neurosurgeons, spine fellowship trained neurosurgeon, academic neurosurgical oncologist, and general neurosurgeon interested in neuro-trauma to join their rapidly growing, comprehensive neuroscience institute. The new Chief, Division of Neurosurgery is seeking interested neurosurgeon(s) in having a robust clinical practice, teaching opportunities, program building, research & device development.
The primary admitting hospital is a very sophisticated, 850+ bed Level I Trauma Center and designated Primary Stroke Center. Organization also comprises three other area hospitals for a total of nearly 1900 beds. The health system is affiliated with the University, offering support/protected time for basic science research interests, medical student and residency teaching opportunities & collaborations with engineering for device development. Hospital is a teaching hospital for numerous residency programs including general surgery and orthopedics, offering residency teaching opportunities.

Hospital & Practice Highlights:
Access to a Gamma Knife;
Varian TrueBeam at the Hospital;
3T MRI;
Epic System for Electronic Medical Records;
Stryker and Stealth Navigation;
9 bed Neuro-ICU with plans to expand to 18 beds;
Busy clinical practice including complex instrumentation, spine deformity & minimally-invasive spine;
Protected time for research including basic science, translational and clinical. New Neurosurgery lab at University (only 15 minutes from the Hospital);
Countless opportunities to do spine outcomes research;
Position will include an academic appointment at the School of Medicine;
Hospital currently running 3-4 Block OR’s 5 days per week specifically for neurosurgery;
Synergies with engineering department create opportunities in bioengineering, biomechanics & new instrument development;
Program building & leadership opportunities including the eventual development of a neurosurgery residency program;
Collaborative support from the Chair of Neurology & Head of Research in development at multi-disciplinary approach to patient care and cutting edge research
Situated within the region, city is a diverse city with a population of almost 850,000. The city is a terrific place to raise a family, offering exceptional public and private schools and home to two major universities. City is the birthplace of aviation and has a tradition of growth and innovation. With over a century of national renown as a center of research and innovation, the city has nationally ranked cultural attractions and is located within an easy drive of many other metropolitan locations.
